replies.body:
An interesting case, but if that's the situation, can't you go out of your way to do a 'jungle roster' update at some point?

There are many champions in the game whose kits make them super weak in lane. {{champion:32}} {{champion:113}} {{champion:11}} {{champion:56}} {{champion:20}} {{champion:19}} {{champion:35}} {{champion:77}} 

However, these champions are not refined for jungling like the champions you started putting out specifically designed for jungling like {{champion:107}} {{champion:121}} {{champion:60}} {{champion:154}} {{champion:79}} {{champion:76}} {{champion:203}} {{champion:421}} {{champion:254}}{{champion:72}}  

These older champions have many things that hold them back from being successful laners but they don't feel nearly as special when they're in their home turf. Skarner gets spires, Rengar can leap from brush to brush, Nidalee had the ability to root monsters, Kindred slows monsters' attack speed...

Nunu is a start. The Consume buff he got where he gets buffs for eating different mobs is unique and clearly ties him to the jungle. What about the other old champions? Any love for them? It wouldn't take much.
